cling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.655856, "shard": "09", "shelf_id": "sn84024808, 1920-10-18, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/mthi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "great falls (mont.)", "cascade", "great falls"], "subject_headings": ["Great Falls (Mont.)--Newspapers", "Montana--Great Falls", "United States--Montana--Cascade--Great Falls"], "subjects": [{"cascade": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:cascade&fo=json"}, {"great falls": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:great+falls&fo=json"}, {"great falls (mont.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:great+falls+%28mont.%29&fo=json"}, {"montana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:montana&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-07-05T16:49:46.303Z", "title": "Great Falls daily tribune (Great Falls, Mont.), October 18, 1920", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/1920-10-18/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84024808"], "batch": ["mthi_alderfly_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1895", "description": ["Daily, 1900-1921 Vol. 9, no. 71 (Mar. 23, 1895)- ; -32nd year (Jan. 10, 1921). Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Great Falls tribune (Great Falls, Mont. : 1921) 2378-850X (DLC)sn 83045217 (OCoLC)9374534"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:15Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-03", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-03"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [47.506453, -111.306019], "location": ["great falls", "cascade", "united states", "montana"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-111.306019, 47.506453], "number": ["2025-05-23t21:30:26", "center for res libr, newsp proj", "1", "2378-833x", "sn86075243", "11299783", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/1921-01-10/ed-1/", "2025-06-25t14:22:47", "sn83045217", "741", "wisconsin hist soc, newsp proj", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/1919-01-01/ed-1/", "sn84024808", "sn86075236", "online resource", "original", "montana hist soc libr", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "microfilm service copy"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "chronicling america", "catalog", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "great falls daily tribune (great falls, mont.) 1895-1921"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 59.08542, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "great falls (mont.)", "cascade", "great falls"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:10:05.966Z", "title": "Great Falls daily tribune", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84024808/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["sutherlin, r. n."], "date": "1875", "dates": ["[1875 TO 1943]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (November 25, 1875); ceased January 7, 1943. \"A Journal Devoted to Agriculture, Livestock, Home Reading, and General News.\". \"Pioneer agricultural and stock journal of Montana.\". Issues from 1925-1943 consists entirely of Montana News Association inserts with no independent content. Place of publication varies: Diamond City, Mont., Nov. 25, 1875-Nov. 20, 1879; White Sulphur Springs, Mont., Dec. 4, 1879-Mar. 24, 1904; Great Falls, Mont., Mar. 31, 1904-Jan. 7, 1943. Editor: R.N. Sutherlin. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 1 (November 25, 1875); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 5, no. 5 (Dec. 18, 1879) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:24.080Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["white sulphur springs", "meagher", "broadwater", "united states", "montana", "great falls", "cascade", "diamond city"], "number": ["online resource", "2332-7537", "862979362", "2013272187", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "rocky mountain husbandman (diamond city, m.t.) 1875-1943 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["electronic journals", "white sulphur springs", "newspapers", "meagher", "broadwater", "united states", "montana", "great falls", "great falls (mont.)", "cascade", "white sulphur springs (mont.)", "diamond city", "diamond city (mont.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "Rocky Mountain husbandman", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272187/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1918]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with volume 2, number 3 (September 14, 1918); ceased October 12, 1918. Official organ of: National Nonpartisan League of the State of Montana. Description based on: Volume 2, number 3 (September 14, 1918); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Volume 2, number 6 (October 5, 1918) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Montana nonpartisan (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["great falls", "cascade", "united states", "montana"], "number": ["online resource", "2014218354", "879343459", "2372-885x", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "montana leader (great falls, montana) 1918-1918 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "national nonpartisan league", "great falls (mont.)", "cascade", "great falls"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "Montana leader", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218354/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1929]"], "description": ["Weekly <Oct. 9-30, 1922> Began with volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918). Ceased in 1922? Last issue located: Vol. 5, no. 8 [i.e. 9] (Oct. 30, 1922). Place of publication varies: Great Falls, Oct. 19, 1918-May 7, 1921; Billings, June 10-<Oct. 30>, 1922. Suspended: Nov. 16-23, 1918; June 1921-May 1922. Official organ of: National Nonpartisan League in the State of Montana. Description based on: Volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Volume 3, number 51 (December 20, 1919) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "cascade", "billings", "great falls"], "number": ["2014218355", "2372-8884", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "879345154", "online resource"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the montana nonpartisan (great falls, montana) 1918-192? [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "national nonpartisan league", "great falls (mont.)", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "cascade", "billings", "great falls"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "The Montana nonpartisan", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218459/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1888", "dates": ["[1888 TO 1900]"], "description": ["Daily (6 times a week) Began with vol. I, no. 20 [i.e. 1] (October 21, 1888); ceased August 23, 1900. Published every morning except Mondays. Weekly editions: Great Falls leader (Great Falls, Mont. : Weekly), 1888-1890; Great Falls weekly leader, 1890- Description based on: Vol. I, no. 20 [i.e. 1] (October 21, 1888); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed August 8, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Vol. II, no. 207 (December 31, 1889) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed August 8, 2014). Great Falls evening leader (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:26.498Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218459/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["great falls", "cascade", "united states", "montana"], "number": ["online resource", "885308774", "2374-1821", "2014218459", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Great Falls daily leader"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the great falls leader (great falls, montana territory) 1888-1900 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 49.941692, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "great falls (mont.)", "cascade", "great falls"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:29.180Z", "title": "The Great Falls leader", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218459/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218460/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1888", "dates": ["[1888 TO 1890]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 1, no. 1 (June 16, 1888); ceased April 9, 1890. Published every Saturday through 1888. Published every Wednesday startin